@flexiarg forward-model/reward-supersedes-evidence
@title Reward Supersedes Evidence
@sigils [⟡/?]
@audience futon stack operators, agents, forward-model authors
@tone conjectural
@style pattern

! conclusion: The rung above empirical-supersedes-logical is learned-reward-supersedes-raw-evidence: a fitted reward model that weighs which observations matter.

  + context: Forward-model hypothesis, not yet attested. Extends the attested ruling that self-model bites must be empirically tested or marked logical.

  + IF:
    The self-model already distinguishes empirically-observed damage from merely-asserted damage, rendering observed conflicts as real and unobserved ones as provisional.

  + HOWEVER:
    Raw evidence is flat, every observation counts equally, so the model cannot tell a load-bearing witness from an incidental one, and cannot generalize across missions.

  + THEN:
    Fit a reward model over the evidence that learns which witnesses reliably predict discharge, conditioned on the kind of mission, and let the learned reward, not raw count, weight the self-model's beliefs, keeping hard anti-gaming gates so the reward cannot be farmed.

  + BECAUSE:
    Evidence-supersedes-assertion made the self-model honest; reward-supersedes-evidence makes it discriminating. Without it the empirical layer plateaus at counting, and the finding that reward is the binding constraint stays unaddressed.

    + evidence: Bridge target, not yet attested. Would connect to the mission-conditional reward mission, the learned-reward line, and the honest-negative finding that reward is the binding constraint.
